[{"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion D\u00fcsseldorf S-2330 A - St 121bek"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "OFD M\u00fcnster S-2251 - 1 - St 11 - 31 vom 22/02 / 79S-2330S-2251EStG: 2/1 / 4EStG: 19 Tax treatment of strike support: Metalworkers strike 1978/79 I am sending you a copy of the IG notification Metall, Executive Board Administration Frankfurt / Main, which IG Metall informs the affected works councils or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "Union shop stewards will be sent about the tax treatment of strike support"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "The communication accurately reflects the legal situation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "Annex: Strike support that a trade union pays its striking members is generally taxable, as is wages paid by the company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "The Federal Fiscal Court decided this in 1970 in a model trial"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "The strike support is then seen as compensation for lost wages and therefore belongs, like this, to the so-called income from employment; In the opinion of the tax authorities, strike support is not taxed at the reduced tax rate provided for \"extraordinary income\" (Section 34 (2) Income Tax Act)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "Naturally, the employer cannot withhold wage tax from the strike support"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "They must therefore be reported to the tax office and taxed when assessing income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "However, taxation by way of an income tax assessment does not actually take place in all cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "In the case of income tax assessment, other income remains (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "from strike support and interest from capital assets) up to certain income limits are not taken into account if this income does not exceed DM 800 in a calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "In addition, an extenuating provision ensures that amounts over DM 800 are taxed less; Taxation only begins in full if the income exceeds DM 1,600 per calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "This DM 800 special regulation does not apply to persons who are taxed as single persons if their income (here: gross income minus all business expenses, special expenses and extraordinary burdens) exceeds DM 24,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to those persons to be assessed together with the spouse whose \"income\" is more than DM 48,000 per calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "It is the same if an assessment for income tax is requested for a special reason, for example to obtain a tax reduction from the \"\u00a7 7b depreciation\" for the single-family house or the condominium"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "The strike support must be indicated in the form for applications for annual income tax adjustment and the income tax return"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "As far as tax information has to be given for the calendar year 1978, only the part of the strike support that was paid out in the period from the start of the strike to December 31, 1978 is of course to be given"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "If the relevant strike support is reported to the tax office, the tax office will usually be asked to provide proof of the strike support paid (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "Receipt or certificate from IG Metall), as the amount of the union fees claimed as income-related expenses gives an indication of the amount of strike support"}, {"meta": {"name": "0047423.xml"}, "text": "Income tax / wage tax / church tax North Rhine-Westphalia strike money strike support"}]